The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to cuts on trees, which are typically studied in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) due to the analysis of the time complexity of the algorithms and the use of game-theoretic concepts in the problem formulation.
